'''Violetta Egorova''' (Russian: Виолетта Викторовна Егорова) is a [[Russians|Russian]] concert [[pianist]].<ref>http://www.forte-piano-pianissimo.com/Great-Women-Pianists.html|title= Great Woman Pianists</ref>

==Biography==
She was born in [[Krasnodar]] on November 16, 1969, a city on the southern most section of Russia. She began to play and improvise on the piano age of four. At the age of six she made her debut on TV, playing pieces from "The Children’s album" by Robert Schumann. Violetta entered the Moscow Central Special Music School for Gifted Children at the age of six, where she studied with A. Artobolevskaya and Alexander Mndoyants.<ref>http://www.mosconsv.ru/ru/person.aspx?id=8871|title= Professor A. Mndoyants</ref> She gave her first solo recital in Moscow, the capital of Russia, at the age twelve.

Ms. Egorova won first place at the Alessandro Casagrande International Piano Competition in Terni,<ref>http://www.concorsocasagrande.org/ita/edizione2.html|title= Casagrande Prize</ref> Italy; G. Viotti International Competition, Italy; Gina Bachauer Piano Competition in USA<ref>http://www.deseretnews.com/article/168553/RUSSIANS-MAKE-MARK-IN-EARLY-BACHAUER-OUTINGS.html?pg=all|title= Article about Competitors</ref> and at many other international competitions. 
Her early career was powered by ability, which she had attained from working with her great mentor [[Lev Naumov]]. Her dedication to the craft fulfilled her mentor's promise, which was to make every note sing. In 1991, while still studying under Professor [[Lev Naumov|Lev Nikolaevich Naymov]] at the [[Moscow Conservatory|P.Tchaikovsky Moscow State Conservatory]],<ref>http://www.mosconsv.ru/ru/students_h.aspx?start=64|title= Student of the Moscow Conservatory</ref><ref>http://www.mosconsv.ru/en/default.aspx|title= Tchaikovsky Conservatory</ref> Art and Electronics, a joint Russian-American recording enterprise, honored Ms. Egorovas talent by recording a CD. This CD contained the music of Mozart and Prokofiev in celebration of the anniversary of those two composers' birth. Furthermore, Ms. Egorova has recorded several CDs under the various labels, such as [[Universal Music Group|Universal Music & V.]],<ref>https://www.amazon.com/Piano-Favorites-Violetta-Egorova/dp/B00000DWDB|title= Violetta Egorova-Piano Favorites</ref> Teichiku Records, Onepoint.fm, Accademia Pianistica Siciliana<ref>http://www.pizzicato.lu/musik-und-schokolade/|title= Musik und Schokolade</ref> and has been featured on radio and television broadcasts in Italy, Turkey, Canada, Egypt, Ecuador, France, and Russia. <br />
[[File:Violetta in concert. Bucharest Phylharmony.jpg|thumb|Violetta in concert. Bucharest Phylharmony]]

Ms. Egorova has performed in some of the most famous concert halls in the United States, Italy, France, Switzerland, Turkey, Egypt, Monaco, Romania, Austria, Russia and China<ref>http://hottingen.ch/files/Klavierkonzert-14.05.09.pdf|title= KLAVIERKONZERT ZÜRICH HOTTINGEN</ref>

She is a regular guest artist with many renowned ensembles such as the [[State Academic Symphony Orchestra of the Russian Federation|State Academic Orchestra of Russia]], [[Utah Symphony Orchestra]], the Chamber Orchestra Kremlin,<ref>http://www.chamberorchestrakremlin.ru/conc/05-06_NC_aug30.htm|title= NIGHTCAP WITH THE CLASSICS</ref> Orchestra del Festival Pianistiñî Internazionale di Bergamo e Brescia, Orchestra Sinfonica di Perogia, The [[George Enescu Philharmonic Orchestra]], [[Cairo Symphony Orchestra]], [[Moscow State Symphony Orchestra|Moscow State Symphonic Orchestra]], as well as the orchestra 'Young Russia', and has played under the direction of [[Pavel Kogan (conductor)|Pavel Kogan]], Joseph Silverstain, Arnold Katz, [[Epifanio Comis]], Mark Gorenstein, Juliano Silvery, Urij Tsuruk, Ilarion Ionescu-Galati, Augustino Orizio and Constantine Orbeljan.

She has also appeared at international musical festivals in Spoletto "Del Due Mondi",<ref>http://www.bibliotecacivica.rovereto.tn.it/UploadDocs/552_InventarioBrunoCagnoli.pdf|title= Del Due Mondi</ref> Sermonette "Pontino di Musica" (Italy), "Sanat Haber" in Istanbul (Turkey), ETNAFEST in Italy, Rachmaninov International festival 2013 in Ukraine. In Moscow, Russia she has done "Grandi Serate Musicali", "Music in Exile", "Music of 20th Century", "Christmas at the Kremlin."<ref>http://www.chamberorchestrakremlin.ru/conc/04-05_Christmas5.htm|title= Ninth Annual Music Festival 
Christmas at the Kremlin</ref>

Ms. Egorova currently is a teacher of Piano High Specialization Courses at the Rachmaninov Academy in Catania, Italy.

Her pianistic repertoire encompasses a wide variety of eras and styles, from concertos and solo monographic works by Bach, Mozart, Beethoven, Schumann, Tchaikovsky, and Liszt to those by contemporary composers.<ref>http://www.ilmoderatore.it/2014/02/08/violetta-egorova-in-concerto-a-palazzo-alliata-19520/|title= Violetta Egorova in concerto a Palazzo Alliata</ref>

Through her well-established relationship with Vladimir Markovich, Eva Gosser, Nina Kotova, Vladislav Bezrukoff, Robin Meyforf, Anna Kruger, Astrid Shvinn, The Lark String Quartet and other musicians, Ms. Egorova has also built a reputation as world-class chamber musician.<ref>http://www.bzb.ro/stire/reprezentatie-de-exceptie-in-marile-serate-muzicale-a66510|title= Marilor Serate Muzicale</ref>

==Awards and outreach==
[[File:Violetta with 2008 Olympic torch.jpg|thumb|With Chinese sportsman Li Yuanlong]]

Violetta Egorova has received many awards and made many television appearances-

In 1990 Violetta won the second prize on Gian Battista Viotti International Music Competition.<ref>http://www.comune.marsala.tp.it/flex/cm/pages/ServeBLOB.php/L/IT/IDPagina/16348|title= Lo spettacolo fa parte del circuito del mito</ref>

In 1991 - Fourth prize on Gina Bachauer International Artists Piano Competition.<ref>http://www.bachauer.com/competitions/past-competitions.html|title= Gina Bachauer Prize</ref>

1992 - First Prize on Alessandro Casagrande International Piano Competition.<ref>http://www.concorsocasagrande.org/ita/edizione2.html|title= Casagrande Prize</ref>

In 2006 - Second Prize of the Sigizmund Thalberg International Piano Competition.<ref>http://www.centrothalberg.it/Winners.html|title= Thalberg Prize</ref>

On 11 July 2008, Violetta carried the Beijing 2008 Olympic torch through Harbin with famous Chinese sportsman Li Yuanlong<ref>http://torchrelay.beijing2008.cn/en/journey/harbin/news/n214447429.shtml|title= Beijing Olympic torch relay kicks off in Harbin</ref>

==Reviews==
[[File:Violetta Egorova in Bucharest.jpg|thumb|Violetta Egorova in Bucharest]]

"...The Russian Pianist Violetta Egorova is an intelligent Creator, and with an absolute Technical superiority in all she can use both skills for her stunning instrument performance. Her dynamic Nuances power is just as phenomenal as the Clarity of the Chords of the fine adjusted Articulation..." - Remy Franck.<ref>http://www.pizzicato.lu/feinjustiert-fur-maximalen-ausdruck/|title= Review on CD Russian Ballet</ref>

"...Her Mozart sounds as an angel's voice in the church..." - E.Dellavalle (Italy)

"…With the first chords of Sonata by Beethoven Violetta Egorova showed complete penetration into the spirit and sense of the music, that drew to her special attention which did not cease in the course of two hours while the concert lasted"                                      -  N.Pulet (France)

"...Egorova's "Erlkoenig" (Schubert-Liszt), here intense and rhapsodic, with some otherworldly soft playing..."  - V.Goodfellow ( USA)<ref>http://www.deseretnews.com/article/168553/RUSSIANS-MAKE-MARK-IN-EARLY-BACHAUER-OUTINGS.html?pg=all|title= Review</ref>

"...pianist’s hands have a language. Romantic expression, impulsive pressure, epic articulation, mincing crispness and daintiness and an abrupt switch to power.... Egorova’s hands spoke beautifully". -S.Belza (Russia)

